targets.context1: Harry had never been to London before.
targets.target: Although Hagrid seemed to know where he was going, he was obviously not used to getting there in an ordinary way.
targets.context2: He got stuck in the ticket barrier on the Underground, and complained loudly that the seats were too small and the trains too slow.

targets.context1: A few old women were sitting in a corner, drinking tiny glasses of sherry.
targets.target: One of them was smoking a long pipe.
targets.context2: A little man in a top hat was talking to the old bartender, who was quite bald and looked like a toothless walnut.

targets.context1: Harry stared as Dumbledore sidled back into the picture on his card and gave him a small smile.
targets.target: Ron was more interested in eating the frogs than looking at the Famous Witches and Wizards cards, but Harry couldn’t keep his eyes off them.
targets.context2: Soon he had not only Dumbledore and Morgana, but Hengist of Woodcroft, Alberic Grunnion, Circe, Paracelsus, and Merlin.
